    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4593: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to"
                            >Wilson</persName>), at Geneva</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 6, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your 56, March 6, 11 a.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>If the Chinese authorities with whom our Minister at Shanghai is to
                        consult in regard to agenda are the highest national Chinese authorities, I
                        feel that my No. 28, March 5, 9 p.m. to you and my instruction to Minister
                            <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">Johnson</persName> of March 5, 9 p.m.<note
                            n="53" xml:id="d559fn53">For Department’s instruction, see telegram No.
                            77 to the Consul General at Shanghai, <ref
                                target="frus1931-41v01#pg_209">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 209</ref>.</note> the text of which
                        was communicated to you in my No. 29, March 5, 10 p.m.,<note n="54"
                            xml:id="d559fn54">No. 29 not printed.</note> sufficiently indicate my
                        views in regard to the points raised in your telegrams 54 and 56.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>It would seem important to get the representatives of the various powers
                        most concerned into conference at Shanghai at the earliest possible
                        moment.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
